    <etym xml:lang="ru">~ Из %iæm-kæl%i(← %iham%i-%ikarya%i-), как <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æppæt"/> из %iæm-kæt%i. Корень %ikar%i- в значении ‘хвалить’ хорошо
        представлен в индоевропейских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><lang/><w>kar-</w></mentioned> (%ičarkarti%i „он прославляет“), <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>κἀῡξ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><w>κήρῡξ</w><gloss><q>глашатай</q></gloss></mentioned>, и др. Неприемлемо со
        звуковой стороны сближение с <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><lang/><w>appello</w><gloss><q>зову</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>E.
                Lewy,</author><ref target="#ref_KZ"/><biblScope>1925 LII
        314</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">From %iæm-kæl%i(← %iham%i-%ikarya%i-), кlike <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æppæt"/> has derived from %iæm-kæt%i. The root %ikar%i- which means 'to
        compliment' is presented in Indo-Euroopean languages: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>kar-</w></mentioned> (%ičarkarti%i 'he praises'), <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>κἀῡξ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><w>κήρῡξ</w><gloss><q>public crier</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc. The
        convergence by sound with <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>appello</w><gloss><q>I
                call</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>E. Lewy,</author><ref target="#ref_KZ"
                /><biblScope>1925 LII 314</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
